@import ./_tui.convo

> user
Animations rendered using inline renders are rendering content outside of side of their
scroll area. The render size they are given needs to be clipped.

Here is an example. The green and black animation is rendering outside of its scroll container.

The issue is only happing when the redner interval calls the callback for rendering. Clipping works
properly in the `drawInlineSprite` function.

![image](data:image/png;base64,)

@time 2026-05-03T14:04:23-04:00
@tokenUsage 31690 / 2691 / $0.171905
@model gpt-5.5-2026-04-23
> assistant
One clarifying question before I update the files:

Should the inline renderer callback receive its `ctx.x/ctx.y` shifted to the visible clipped area, with `ctx.width/ctx.height` reduced to that clipped region?

That would mean if a renderer’s natural inline area starts above/left of a scroll viewport, the callback only sees the visible clipped rectangle. This matches “the render size they are given needs to be clipped” and prevents interval renders from writing outside the scroll area.


> user
`ctx.x` and `ctx.y` do not need to change. `ctx.width` and `ctx.height` need to be adjusted to match
the height after clipping.

@time 2026-05-03T14:09:50-04:00
@tokenUsage 31834 / 8204 / $0.20019
@model gpt-5.5-2026-04-23
> assistant
I’ll update the inline renderer animation context so interval renders keep an internal clip and use clipped diff/copy bounds. This keeps `ctx.x`/`ctx.y` unchanged while reducing `ctx.width`/`ctx.height` to the clipped render area.

